WEBVTT

00:01.218 --> 00:02.350
- Previously on
"Superman and Lois"...

00:02.393 --> 00:03.481
- That feeling to give
into the disease

00:03.525 --> 00:04.830
gets to be so strong.

00:04.874 --> 00:06.528
This drive that your wife has,

00:06.571 --> 00:09.096
she's gonna need to use
all that energy to survive.

00:09.139 --> 00:10.967
- I'm not okay with Lois
getting her treatment

00:11.011 --> 00:12.838
at Bruno Mannheim's hospital.

00:12.882 --> 00:14.318
- Being a patient here
will allow me

00:14.362 --> 00:15.928
to move around more freely.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.887
I can get access
to Dr. Hook's files.

00:17.930 --> 00:19.932
You have Superman's blood,

00:19.976 --> 00:23.327
and you're having Dr. Hook
use it to make powered people

00:23.371 --> 00:25.677
like Henry Miller.
- The only thing I'm doing here

00:25.721 --> 00:27.157
is trying to save lives.

00:27.201 --> 00:28.941
- While you were
fighting Deadline,

00:28.985 --> 00:30.595
Intergang was silently
raiding the cupboards.

00:30.639 --> 00:31.770
- What did they take?

00:31.814 --> 00:34.034
- This is our new priority.

00:34.077 --> 00:36.471
[dramatic music]

00:36.514 --> 00:38.429
- Uh, hi, I'm Clark.

00:38.473 --> 00:40.866
My wife, Lois,
has breast cancer.

00:40.910 --> 00:44.827
She's been coming here,
to Hob's Bay, for chemo,

00:44.870 --> 00:46.655
and, uh,

00:46.698 --> 00:48.091
thanks for having me.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.223
- Who'd like to start?

00:51.007 --> 00:53.053
Avi, how's Raj?

00:53.096 --> 00:55.881
- Oh, still a big baby.

00:55.925 --> 00:56.969
Surgery went well,

00:57.013 --> 00:58.928
but the recovery is long.

00:58.971 --> 01:00.756
So now, I'm doing everything.

01:00.799 --> 01:03.324
- The burden on a spouseis real,

01:03.367 --> 01:06.457
and it's healthy
to be honest about it.

01:06.501 --> 01:08.111
Have you told Raj how you feel?

01:08.155 --> 01:10.244
- Oh, how I feel is
I never should've let him

01:10.287 --> 01:12.115
move his big dumb TV
into the bedroom.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.335
- [laughs]
Talk to him.

01:14.378 --> 01:16.728
Something tells me
he'll surprise you.

01:19.514 --> 01:23.257
Victor, how are things at home?

01:23.300 --> 01:25.781
- I guess I'm just trying
to count my blessings.

01:25.824 --> 01:29.480
Nancy's last scan
was better than expected,

01:29.524 --> 01:31.656
but her doc keeps warning me

01:31.700 --> 01:33.615
someday soon
that won't be the case.

01:35.920 --> 01:38.098
[whimpers]

01:38.140 --> 01:41.144
And I don't know
how I'll be able to face it.

01:43.799 --> 01:46.801
The end.
- We can't, really,

01:46.845 --> 01:48.412
until it's our turn.

01:48.456 --> 01:51.720
♪ ♪

01:51.763 --> 01:55.245
I haven't shared this
in a while, but

01:55.289 --> 01:59.684
six years ago, my husband was
diagnosed with colon cancer.

01:59.728 --> 02:01.643
Dan was a runner--

02:01.686 --> 02:04.211
4 a.m., six days a week.

02:04.254 --> 02:06.691
Through chemo
and all the surgeries,

02:06.735 --> 02:09.738
he kept getting back out there.

02:09.781 --> 02:11.305
He was my miracle...

02:13.568 --> 02:15.004
Until he wasn't.

02:17.485 --> 02:20.140
He was told
the end was inevitable,

02:20.183 --> 02:22.838
but Dan had no quit in him.

02:25.101 --> 02:28.365
Even as the chemo

02:28.409 --> 02:30.541
took his body

02:30.585 --> 02:32.021
and the pain

02:32.064 --> 02:34.502
became a constant,

02:34.545 --> 02:36.156
he pressed on.

02:38.767 --> 02:41.509
And one day, I realized

02:41.552 --> 02:44.207
he was only doing it--

02:44.251 --> 02:46.644
hanging on--

02:46.688 --> 02:49.125
for me.

02:49.168 --> 02:52.084
[sighs]
So

02:52.128 --> 02:54.739
I sat beside him,

02:54.783 --> 02:55.827
took his hand...

02:59.744 --> 03:03.183
And I told Dan that it's okay

03:03.226 --> 03:04.358
to let go.

03:04.401 --> 03:08.318
♪ ♪

03:08.362 --> 03:10.842
- So he went to group therapy?
Good for him.

03:10.886 --> 03:12.366
- It's good for both of us.

03:12.409 --> 03:14.629
- Dr. Hook's research files,
as requested,

03:14.672 --> 03:16.848
and Mr. Mannheim wishes
you well on your article.

03:16.892 --> 03:18.807
[pen clicks]

03:18.850 --> 03:20.200
- Thank you.

03:20.243 --> 03:21.897
- You're doing a story
on Dr. Hook?

03:21.940 --> 03:23.638
- More like Hob's Bay.

03:23.681 --> 03:25.335
- Oh, what's your angle?

03:25.379 --> 03:26.771
- Depends on what I find.

03:26.815 --> 03:28.469
- If there's anything I can do,

03:28.512 --> 03:30.775
lucky for you, I am
born and raised right here.

03:30.819 --> 03:32.734
- I might take you up on that.

03:32.777 --> 03:35.606
- Your next treatment's
what number--number three?

03:35.650 --> 03:38.478
- Four--over halfway.

03:38.522 --> 03:41.264
- Four was when
my taste buds went to hell.

03:41.308 --> 03:43.962
Let me take you out before
you can't get anything down--

03:44.006 --> 03:45.529
and you could ask me
all about Hob's Bay.

03:47.836 --> 03:48.966
- Hi there.

03:49.011 --> 03:50.404
- Done already?

03:50.447 --> 03:51.970
- It's good to see you again.

03:52.014 --> 03:53.537
- I hear you're doing group.
That's great.

03:53.581 --> 03:55.060
It really helped my husband.

03:55.103 --> 03:56.540
- Oh.

03:56.584 --> 03:58.063
These the files?
- Yeah.

03:58.107 --> 04:05.114
♪ ♪

04:07.029 --> 04:08.509
- I'd love to get a meal.

04:08.552 --> 04:10.250
- It's a date.

04:10.293 --> 04:14.297
♪ ♪

04:14.341 --> 04:16.168
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine--

04:16.212 --> 04:18.214
just wasn't for me.

04:18.257 --> 04:22.740
♪ ♪

04:22.784 --> 04:25.743
[heroic music]

04:25.787 --> 04:29.965
♪ ♪

04:30.008 --> 04:32.402
- But you said
we'd watch a movie.

04:32.446 --> 04:33.621
- I know, honey,

04:33.664 --> 04:35.623
and I'm not happy
about it either,

04:35.666 --> 04:38.190
but there's a huge mess
at work that can't wait

04:38.234 --> 04:40.367
until Monday.
- Can I come with you?

04:40.409 --> 04:42.673
- Oh, honey, I am already
late for an interview

04:42.717 --> 04:44.240
with Chrissy Beppo
from "The Gazette,"

04:44.284 --> 04:46.590
and then I have
meetings all day,

04:46.634 --> 04:48.375
but maybe you and your sister

04:48.418 --> 04:50.072
can do something fun today.

04:50.115 --> 04:51.856
- What?
No, I--Mom, I have to study

04:51.900 --> 04:53.858
for my geometry midterm.

04:53.902 --> 04:56.252
Why can't Dad take her?
- Um, it's not his day,

04:56.296 --> 04:58.385
but if you wanna ask him,
be my guest.

04:58.428 --> 04:59.429
[smooches]

05:01.649 --> 05:03.128
- Are you serious?

05:03.172 --> 05:05.087
- I believe in you.
I love you.

05:05.130 --> 05:08.090
[dramatic music]

05:08.133 --> 05:09.091
♪ ♪

05:09.134 --> 05:10.092
- You wanna play a game

05:10.135 --> 05:11.223
I downloaded?

05:11.267 --> 05:13.138
You get chased by zombie cats.

05:13.182 --> 05:16.228
- Soph, I'm, like, up to my
ears in trapezoids right now--

05:16.272 --> 05:18.535
maybe later.

05:18.579 --> 05:25.586
♪ ♪

05:26.717 --> 05:28.415
- Chrissy!

05:28.457 --> 05:30.112
- Ms. Mayor--uh, Lana.

05:30.155 --> 05:31.113
Hi.
[chuckles]

05:31.156 --> 05:32.114
- I am so sorry

05:32.157 --> 05:33.245
to keep you waiting.

05:33.289 --> 05:34.508
There just never seems

05:34.551 --> 05:36.205
to be enough time anymore.

05:36.248 --> 05:38.860
- Yeah, tell me about it,
girlfriend.

05:38.903 --> 05:42.342
I mean, you're mayor,
and now you're a single mom.

05:42.385 --> 05:44.735
I mean, it must be
so hard to do it all.

05:44.779 --> 05:46.520
I--I'd forget to eat my lunch

05:46.563 --> 05:48.217
if Lois didn't remind me.

05:48.260 --> 05:50.915
- Um, yeah...

05:50.959 --> 05:52.961
No, it's difficult, sure.

05:53.004 --> 05:56.399
Uh, it's more just that, um,

05:56.443 --> 05:57.618
it's weird.

05:57.661 --> 05:58.880
I mean, Kyle and I

05:58.923 --> 06:00.185
are still trying to figure out

06:00.229 --> 06:01.883
the whole co-parenting thing,

06:01.926 --> 06:04.451
and it's just...

06:06.104 --> 06:08.193
[chuckles]
Wow, I've turned

06:08.237 --> 06:09.891
into that divorced person

06:09.934 --> 06:11.501
people cross the street
to avoid.

06:11.545 --> 06:13.460
- No.

06:13.503 --> 06:16.637
No worries--it's all good.

06:16.680 --> 06:19.161
Um, so you said
that you had a statement

06:19.204 --> 06:21.381
about the new town hall?

06:22.686 --> 06:24.122
- I look like
a deflated balloon.

06:25.776 --> 06:27.865
- I guess it's vintage?

06:27.909 --> 06:30.302
- Mr. Cushing says I gotta
wear a trainee uniform

06:30.346 --> 06:31.521
until I earn a better one.

06:31.565 --> 06:32.740
- Who's Rusty?

06:32.783 --> 06:33.957
- I don't know, but the crew

06:34.002 --> 06:35.482
keeps saying he died in these.

06:36.831 --> 06:38.354
[air booms]

06:38.398 --> 06:40.356
- Dad, I beat
the last fortress hologram,

06:40.400 --> 06:43.185
and it was that
Kryptonian martial arts lady.

06:43.228 --> 06:46.188
You look like a guy who made
a wish to be a kid again.

06:46.231 --> 06:47.450
- Hilarious.

06:47.494 --> 06:49.321
I have to go.
If I'm late,

06:49.365 --> 06:51.411
the crew might make me dress up
as a dalmatian or something.

06:51.454 --> 06:53.151
- Hey, it might
be an improvement.

06:53.195 --> 06:55.502
[chuckles]

06:55.545 --> 06:56.938
- Take it easy on him.

06:56.981 --> 06:58.548
He's training just like you.

06:58.592 --> 06:59.593
- All right, well,
Dad said that after I win

06:59.636 --> 07:00.681
the last hologram fight,

07:00.724 --> 07:02.030
that I can actually do some

07:02.073 --> 07:03.640
saves on my own.
- That is not even close

07:03.684 --> 07:04.989
to what I said.
I'm sure it's what you wanted

07:05.033 --> 07:08.993
to hear me say, but--
[whirring]

07:09.037 --> 07:10.473
It's your dad.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.170
Something's happening
with Deadline.

07:12.214 --> 07:13.607
- It's been over a month
since you've fought him.

07:13.650 --> 07:15.086
Maybe he's finally
ready to talk.

07:15.130 --> 07:16.784
- Well, whatever it is,
it sounds urgent.

07:16.827 --> 07:18.046
You coming with?

07:18.089 --> 07:19.395
- Maybe you should go ahead.

07:19.439 --> 07:20.570
I kind of overdid it a little.

07:20.614 --> 07:22.267
Plus, I have plenty to do here.

07:22.311 --> 07:23.747
- Can I go?

07:23.791 --> 07:24.922
Just for backup.

07:24.966 --> 07:26.358
- Stay here with your mom.

07:26.402 --> 07:27.534
We'll talk
about your training later.

07:27.577 --> 07:28.839
[air booms]

07:28.883 --> 07:33.540
♪ ♪

07:33.582 --> 07:35.498
- Mr. Distefano insists

07:35.542 --> 07:37.021
he'll only talk to you.

07:37.065 --> 07:38.240
- Why the change of heart?

07:38.283 --> 07:39.546
- He says he's sick.

07:39.589 --> 07:40.590
[security panel beeps]

07:42.374 --> 07:44.072
- [struggling]
Superman,

07:44.115 --> 07:46.466
take me to Bruno Mannheim.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.293
- Seems pretty fishy to me.
- [coughs]

07:48.337 --> 07:51.383
- It's not.
He's got tumors everywhere.

07:51.427 --> 07:52.602
What did Mannheim do to you?

07:52.646 --> 07:54.604
- Please--
[groans loudly]

07:54.648 --> 07:57.477
Take me, or I'll die.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.609
[groans]
- Take him.

07:59.653 --> 08:01.045
[air booms]

08:08.096 --> 08:09.924
- Mannheim!

08:09.967 --> 08:12.274
- You're crossing the red line
coming back here.

08:12.317 --> 08:13.971
He's dying.
He says only you can save him.

08:14.015 --> 08:17.888
- I didn't tell him anything.
[coughing]

08:17.932 --> 08:20.325
- Bruno, you're killing him.
- What do you want from me?

08:20.369 --> 08:22.066
I'm not a doctor.
- His body is tearing

08:22.110 --> 08:23.503
itself apart.

08:23.546 --> 08:25.287
- Then you should
take him to a hospital.

08:25.330 --> 08:28.377
♪ ♪

08:28.420 --> 08:30.161
[air booms]

08:36.298 --> 08:39.256
[country music]

08:39.301 --> 08:46.351
♪ ♪

08:57.841 --> 08:59.234
- Yo, Rusty Nail,

08:59.277 --> 09:02.933
I think you missed a spot.

09:02.977 --> 09:06.023
- Your dad has had me
washing this truck all day.

09:06.067 --> 09:08.373
Okay, every time that
I think I'm finished,

09:08.417 --> 09:10.767
he somehow finds a smudge
and makes me start over.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.813
Okay, I think
I'm losing my mind.

09:12.856 --> 09:14.423
- Yeah, well, that sounds
better than studying

09:14.466 --> 09:16.643
parallelograms for eight hours.

09:16.686 --> 09:17.948
- That's this Monday.

09:17.992 --> 09:19.036
- Yeah.

09:20.472 --> 09:21.778
- Welp,
I'm gonna be a sophomore

09:21.822 --> 09:22.997
for the rest of my life.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.825
- I'm hitting it hard tomorrow,

09:24.868 --> 09:26.043
if you wanted to join me.

09:26.087 --> 09:27.784
- Hey, mijita, let's, uh,

09:27.828 --> 09:30.178
let's not distract
Rusty Buckets here

09:30.221 --> 09:31.222
while he's in training mode.

09:31.266 --> 09:32.963
- Okay, can I, at least,

09:33.007 --> 09:35.096
just get a shirt with
my real name on it, please?

09:35.139 --> 09:37.751
- See, that's the--that's
the deal with your generation

09:37.794 --> 09:39.100
right there, right?
Y'all just--y'all just

09:39.143 --> 09:40.536
wanna skip right to the top

09:40.580 --> 09:42.277
with a little dance move,
little cat memes,

09:42.320 --> 09:44.584
something like that.
Naw, you're Rusty

09:44.627 --> 09:46.498
till I say otherwise.

09:46.542 --> 09:47.717
- [sighs] Okay.

09:47.761 --> 09:49.197
- Okay, come on, Soph,

09:49.240 --> 09:50.502
Mom's making dinner.

09:50.546 --> 09:52.330
- But we didn't
get to do anything.

09:54.506 --> 09:56.944
- Um, I'm at work, sweetie.

09:56.987 --> 09:58.423
I--what'd you expect?

09:58.467 --> 09:59.990
- I don't know--

10:00.034 --> 10:01.731
something fun.

10:01.775 --> 10:03.907
When's the fair coming?

10:03.951 --> 10:06.170
- Not till summer.

10:06.214 --> 10:09.391
Hey, look, I promise
I'll take you then, okay?

10:09.434 --> 10:13.569
♪ ♪

10:13.613 --> 10:15.615
- It's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.094
Soph.

10:17.138 --> 10:18.792
Wait.

10:20.184 --> 10:22.491
- All right, chop, chop,
Crusty Rusty.

10:22.534 --> 10:24.406
Let's see what you got there.

10:24.449 --> 10:26.887
I'm not paying you
nothing to stand around.

10:26.930 --> 10:30.542
All right, put your shoulder
into it a little bit.

10:30.586 --> 10:31.631
[air booms]

10:32.893 --> 10:34.459
- Deadline died?
- They definitely had a deal,

10:34.503 --> 10:36.636
but Mannheim wouldn't admit it,

10:36.679 --> 10:38.463
and then it was too late.

10:38.507 --> 10:39.987
- Before Bruno
had him released,

10:40.030 --> 10:42.076
James Distefano
was diagnosed in prison

10:42.119 --> 10:43.686
with stage four lymphoma.

10:43.730 --> 10:45.819
The only other prisoner
who got out early

10:45.862 --> 10:48.430
was also terminal--
- Was Henry Miller--

10:48.473 --> 10:49.910
right before
he showed up with powers.

10:49.953 --> 10:52.173
- And when the DOD took
Distefano into custody,

10:52.216 --> 10:54.741
he had traces of X-K
and your blood

10:54.784 --> 10:57.004
in his system.
- So Mannheim's what,

10:57.047 --> 10:59.223
giving powers
to dying criminals?

10:59.267 --> 11:00.224
I mean,
why go through the trouble?

11:00.268 --> 11:01.443
- What if--and I know

11:01.486 --> 11:02.705
it's a big if--it's Mannheim--

11:02.749 --> 11:05.403
but what if
this isn't about powers?

11:05.447 --> 11:07.623
What if he's actually trying
to keep these guys alive?

11:07.667 --> 11:08.668
[door clicks]

11:09.756 --> 11:11.148
No!
Carpet--uh-uh.

11:11.192 --> 11:12.497
- Where were you?
- There was a flash flood

11:12.541 --> 11:14.456
in Utah.
It was like a wall of water

11:14.499 --> 11:16.066
and trees
and all kinds of stuff.

11:16.110 --> 11:17.546
I mean, like, I--I saved, like,

11:17.589 --> 11:19.374
this hiker
and maybe a yoga instructor.

11:19.417 --> 11:21.202
It was nuts!

11:21.245 --> 11:23.160
- Jordan, how many times
do I have to say it?

11:23.204 --> 11:24.596
No saves without me.

11:24.640 --> 11:26.076
- Babe, wait--
- No, we still don't know

11:26.120 --> 11:27.164
your limits.
What if you would've

11:27.208 --> 11:28.339
gotten hurt or worse?

11:29.384 --> 11:31.038
- I told him he could go.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.389
I know--I'm sorry.

11:34.432 --> 11:36.608
It was just a flood.
I thought he'd be okay,

11:36.652 --> 11:38.480
and there wasn't time
to check with you.

11:40.525 --> 11:41.875
- You think you're ready?

11:41.918 --> 11:43.398
Tomorrow, it's you and me
at the fortress.

11:43.441 --> 11:45.139
- Yeah?
Th--th--that's awesome.

11:45.182 --> 11:48.055
Thanks, Dad.
- Yeah, now go shower.

11:48.098 --> 11:49.447
- Carpet!
- Watch the mud--the mud!

11:49.491 --> 11:50.884
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.

11:50.927 --> 11:53.625
[dramatic music]

11:53.669 --> 11:56.237
- Blend of Kryptonite
and Superman's blood

11:56.280 --> 11:58.892
in our new subject
has incredible potential

11:58.935 --> 12:00.502
to reanimate cells.

12:00.545 --> 12:02.156
- Potential isn't good enough.

12:02.199 --> 12:03.679
I need the new serum.

12:03.723 --> 12:05.028
- And you'll have it,

12:05.072 --> 12:07.204
as long as Lois Lane
stops poking around

12:07.248 --> 12:08.989
Hob's Bay Medical.
- Don't worry.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.426
She'll be up to her ears
in admin records.

12:11.469 --> 12:12.732
- What about Superman?

12:12.775 --> 12:14.734
He showed up
to your office again.

12:14.777 --> 12:16.213
If he finds us down here--

12:16.257 --> 12:17.432
- Focus on the work.

12:17.475 --> 12:18.825
Let me handle Superman.

12:18.868 --> 12:24.091
♪ ♪

12:24.134 --> 12:25.657
- [echoing] This is reckless.

12:25.701 --> 12:28.051
- We either make our move now

12:28.095 --> 12:29.836
or let Superman make his.

12:29.879 --> 12:31.925
- We only have one shot.

12:31.968 --> 12:34.057
- Then make sure
you don't miss.

12:34.101 --> 12:37.974
[suspenseful music]

12:38.018 --> 12:40.934
[smooching]

12:47.723 --> 12:48.811
- What?

12:48.855 --> 12:50.421
Was it...

12:50.465 --> 12:52.293
oh, garlic.
Ah, okay.

12:52.336 --> 12:54.774
Here, let me add another mint,
at least.

12:56.732 --> 12:58.255
- [sighs]
I interviewed Lana today.

13:03.304 --> 13:04.696
Yeah, and the whole time,

13:04.740 --> 13:06.437
I couldn't stop
thinking about you.

13:08.439 --> 13:11.355
- Sweet.
- [chuckles]

13:11.399 --> 13:14.532
No, but no, it was...

13:14.576 --> 13:16.491
[sighs]
It was awful.

13:16.534 --> 13:19.450
It was like I was trapped
in some Edgar Allan Poe story,

13:19.494 --> 13:21.801
and she could hear my heart
beating out of my chest.

13:23.933 --> 13:25.065
- Why can't we just tell her?

13:25.108 --> 13:26.544
- I get it.

13:26.588 --> 13:27.937
I do.

13:27.981 --> 13:29.983
Okay?
But it's just...

13:30.026 --> 13:32.072
it's so soon after the divorce.

13:32.115 --> 13:34.335
- Kyle, I don't want
to be some side piece.

13:34.378 --> 13:35.640
- No--oh, no.

13:35.684 --> 13:38.687
You are not a side piece.

13:42.386 --> 13:44.867
I just don't want
anyone to get hurt,

13:44.911 --> 13:46.086
especially my girls.

13:46.129 --> 13:47.609
I...

13:47.652 --> 13:49.829
I put 'em
through enough already.

13:53.136 --> 13:55.530
Can you just give me
a little more time, babe?

13:55.573 --> 13:58.446
- [chuckles]
I like when you call me "babe."

13:58.489 --> 14:00.230
- Oh, do you?
- Mm-hmm.

14:00.274 --> 14:02.276
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

14:02.319 --> 14:05.366
- Well, uh, hey...

14:07.934 --> 14:10.893
[dramatic music]

14:10.937 --> 14:12.199
♪ ♪

14:12.242 --> 14:14.157
- Hey, is everything okay?

14:14.201 --> 14:17.726
- James Distefano
had three girls.

14:17.769 --> 14:18.945
- [sighs]

14:18.988 --> 14:20.076
- I know he was trouble,

14:20.120 --> 14:22.557
but they lost their dad today.

14:22.600 --> 14:23.863
It's so sad.

14:26.561 --> 14:28.084
- Estate planning?
What's this?

14:28.128 --> 14:30.043
- Something we should've
done so long ago--

14:30.086 --> 14:32.349
it is embarrassing.

14:32.393 --> 14:34.438
- "Healthcare
Power of Attorney,"

14:34.482 --> 14:35.962
"Last Will and Testament,"

14:36.005 --> 14:37.311
"End of Life Decisions"?

14:37.354 --> 14:38.878
Lois--
- This does not have to be

14:38.921 --> 14:40.618
a big deal, but today,
if nothing else,

14:40.662 --> 14:42.490
was a reminder
that we need to be ready

14:42.533 --> 14:44.013
just in case.
- There's no reason

14:44.057 --> 14:45.101
for any of this.
- Except for the fact

14:45.145 --> 14:46.189
that I have cancer,

14:46.233 --> 14:47.321
a disease that killed a man

14:47.364 --> 14:48.670
in front of you this morning.

14:48.713 --> 14:49.627
- Yeah, I know,
but that was different.

14:49.671 --> 14:50.977
- How?

14:51.020 --> 14:52.674
- He was one
of Mannheim's test subjects.

14:52.717 --> 14:54.850
I mean, who knows what other
chemicals he was exposed to.

14:54.894 --> 14:56.286
Besides, babe,
you're young and strong,

14:56.330 --> 14:57.635
and I know
you're gonna get through this.

14:57.679 --> 14:58.898
- Clark, can you
at least consider--

14:58.941 --> 14:59.899
- Nope.
[smooches]

14:59.942 --> 15:01.422
I don't have to.

15:01.465 --> 15:03.119
- Clark, come on.

15:03.163 --> 15:04.904
- Look, babe, if you wanna
have these papers in order

15:04.947 --> 15:06.253
and that makes you feel better,
fine,

15:06.296 --> 15:08.820
but I'm telling you
it's not necessary.

15:08.864 --> 15:15.915
♪ ♪

15:20.963 --> 15:23.923
[computer hologram whirring]

15:23.966 --> 15:26.926
[dramatic music]

15:26.969 --> 15:31.756
♪ ♪

15:31.800 --> 15:32.801
- See?

15:32.844 --> 15:34.455
Told you I'm ready.

15:34.498 --> 15:35.935
- [sighs]
Well, it's a good start,

15:35.978 --> 15:38.328
but simulations
can only tell us so much.

15:38.372 --> 15:39.982
- Come on.
I've literally done everything

15:40.026 --> 15:41.375
you've asked.
- Look, Jordan,

15:41.418 --> 15:42.724
you're still growing,
and you're only

15:42.767 --> 15:43.943
half-Kryptonian.
We still don't know

15:43.986 --> 15:45.031
all of your vulnerabilities.

15:45.074 --> 15:46.336
- Or how strong I am.

15:46.380 --> 15:47.468
- It's not
just about strength.

15:47.511 --> 15:48.599
It's about risk assessment,

15:48.643 --> 15:50.079
tactics, experience.

15:50.123 --> 15:51.341
- Okay, how am I
supposed to get experience

15:51.385 --> 15:52.342
if you won't even let me try?

15:52.386 --> 15:53.604
- You'll get your chance.

15:53.648 --> 15:54.692
You just have to be patient.

15:54.736 --> 15:56.390
- I've been patient.

15:56.433 --> 15:58.087
You can't hold me back
just 'cause you're afraid.

16:00.133 --> 16:02.048
I didn't mean that.

16:02.091 --> 16:03.440
- You really think
you're ready?

16:03.484 --> 16:04.615
Okay.

16:04.659 --> 16:06.661
[hologram whirs]

16:06.704 --> 16:08.054
- I've already beat him.

16:08.097 --> 16:09.577
- Well then,
let's crank it up a notch.

16:09.620 --> 16:12.623
[hologram whirring]

16:15.409 --> 16:16.845
- All right.

16:16.888 --> 16:18.890
Bring it.

16:18.934 --> 16:21.937
♪ ♪

16:21.981 --> 16:23.591
[air booms]
- I'm impressed.

16:23.634 --> 16:25.114
Online,
it says a two-month wait.

16:26.898 --> 16:29.292
- There you go.
- Thanks, Tom.

16:29.336 --> 16:31.642
- Has this place
always been here?

16:31.686 --> 16:32.992
- In one form or another.

16:34.950 --> 16:38.084
I remember
when it had red leather booths,

16:38.127 --> 16:41.087
and you could
bring your own wine--ugh...

16:41.130 --> 16:42.653
- It's been a while
since I've felt hungry,

16:42.697 --> 16:44.481
but I'm excited to try it.
It looks amazing.

16:44.525 --> 16:46.614
- It really is.

16:46.657 --> 16:47.963
Why am I doing this to myself?

16:48.007 --> 16:49.356
[chuckles]

16:49.399 --> 16:51.923
It's okay.
I knew what i was getting into.

16:51.967 --> 16:53.316
- Are you sure
you're okay if I--

16:53.360 --> 16:55.797
- No, please--
I'm just happy you're here.

16:55.840 --> 16:58.495
- Me too.
I really needed this.

16:58.539 --> 16:59.975
So is it that obvious?

17:00.019 --> 17:01.846
- Ooh, I'd recognize that look

17:01.890 --> 17:04.240
on your
husband's face anywhere.

17:04.284 --> 17:05.849
Okay, let me guess--

17:05.894 --> 17:06.938
"Everything is okay."

17:06.982 --> 17:08.330
- Yes!
If Clark says,

17:08.375 --> 17:09.723
"It's all gonna be fine"
one more time,

17:09.767 --> 17:11.073
I might actually lose it.

17:11.117 --> 17:12.291
- It's bad enough other people

17:12.335 --> 17:13.467
always insist on saying that,

17:13.510 --> 17:15.946
but at home too?
It's exhausting.

17:15.991 --> 17:17.079
- Clark's amazing,

17:17.123 --> 17:18.079
and he is the most optimistic

17:18.124 --> 17:19.777
person I have ever met.

17:19.820 --> 17:21.083
It's one of the things
I love the most about him,

17:21.127 --> 17:24.608
but anytime I even acknowledge

17:24.652 --> 17:27.523
that not everyone beats cancer,

17:27.568 --> 17:29.048
he just refuses to believe

17:29.091 --> 17:31.006
that I could be one of them.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.399
- For you and me,
that's a reality

17:32.442 --> 17:35.228
we have to face
all day, every day.

17:35.271 --> 17:37.578
For everyone else

17:37.621 --> 17:40.842
to really get that...

17:40.885 --> 17:42.931
I've been in this a long time.

17:42.974 --> 17:45.455
My husband's still
getting his head around it.

17:45.499 --> 17:46.630
- How do you handle it?

17:46.674 --> 17:47.849
- I remember
he's doing his best

17:47.892 --> 17:49.503
and try to be patient,

17:49.546 --> 17:51.461
and other times, I yell.

17:51.505 --> 17:52.462
[chuckles]
A lot.

17:52.506 --> 17:56.205
♪ ♪

17:56.249 --> 17:57.206
[phone keyboard clicking]

17:57.250 --> 18:00.253
- [whistling]

18:02.733 --> 18:05.388
[hums]

18:05.432 --> 18:06.433
- You're chipper.

18:06.476 --> 18:08.522
It's weird.

18:08.565 --> 18:10.001
- Hey, sun is out,

18:10.045 --> 18:11.916
and the day is upon us.

18:11.960 --> 18:13.353
What more can you ask for?

18:13.396 --> 18:15.659
[chuckles]
[knocking at door]

18:15.703 --> 18:17.966
Oh, Trusty Rusty!

18:18.009 --> 18:19.837
No training today.

18:19.881 --> 18:23.058
- Actually, I'm here to study
with Sarah if that's okay.

18:23.102 --> 18:25.365
- Oh, yeah, by all means.

18:25.408 --> 18:26.844
Uh, keep an eye
on your sister for me.

18:26.888 --> 18:28.890
Okay?
I'll be right back.

18:28.933 --> 18:31.066
Russell, hasta luego.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.111
[clicks tongue]

18:33.329 --> 18:34.852
- Uh... [chuckles]
I don't know.

18:37.768 --> 18:38.900
- Did Dad leave?

18:38.943 --> 18:40.510
- Do you see him here?

18:40.554 --> 18:42.686
- But I'm hungry.
- Sophie, we gotta study.

18:42.730 --> 18:44.471
If you're hungry,
then go get something to eat.

18:44.514 --> 18:51.521
♪ ♪

18:57.353 --> 18:59.268
- This tortellini was magical.

19:00.748 --> 19:02.053
Just wish I had my appetite.

19:02.097 --> 19:04.708
How have I never
heard of this place?

19:04.752 --> 19:07.058
- Oh, no one really
paid attention to Hob's Bay--

19:07.102 --> 19:08.147
until recently.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.626
- Seems like Bruno Mannheim

19:09.670 --> 19:11.106
likes to take
most of the credit for that.

19:11.150 --> 19:13.195
- Well, I mean, it's not wrong.

19:13.239 --> 19:15.458
Look at what he's done
for the schools--

19:15.502 --> 19:18.287
and all the new parks,
the hospital.

19:18.331 --> 19:20.115
It's his investments that
brought this neighborhood

19:20.159 --> 19:21.464
back to life.
- Yeah, but where'd

19:21.508 --> 19:24.032
all that money come from?

19:24.075 --> 19:25.903
I can't prove it yet,
but I think the hospital's

19:25.947 --> 19:27.470
a cover for something.

19:27.514 --> 19:30.081
- You mean something bad?

19:30.125 --> 19:32.171
- Too soon to tell.

19:32.214 --> 19:35.391
- You're basing this theory on,
what, a feeling?

19:35.435 --> 19:36.827
- The same one that has led me

19:36.871 --> 19:38.699
to every big story
I've ever broken.

19:38.742 --> 19:41.092
- Yeah, I'm not about
to argue with Lois Lane,

19:41.136 --> 19:42.920
but the hospital has done

19:42.964 --> 19:45.619
so much good for so many--

19:45.662 --> 19:47.490
I mean, including you.
[chuckles]

19:47.534 --> 19:50.667
And--and--and
the doctors there--

19:50.711 --> 19:51.973
five years ago, they--

19:52.016 --> 19:54.671
they took--they took the time.

19:54.715 --> 19:56.369
They cared.

19:56.412 --> 19:59.110
They caught things
that my first team missed.

19:59.154 --> 20:00.895
If they hadn't,
I wouldn't be here.

20:00.938 --> 20:02.505
[chuckles]
So it's hard for me

20:02.549 --> 20:03.854
just to imagine
them doing something

20:03.898 --> 20:06.683
that could hurt people.

20:06.727 --> 20:08.685
- You're right, and I'm sorry.
- No, it's--don't be--

20:08.729 --> 20:11.210
always surprises me
how it all comes flooding back.

20:13.386 --> 20:15.214
[sighs]

20:15.257 --> 20:16.215
- Thank you.

20:16.258 --> 20:19.392
♪ ♪

20:19.435 --> 20:21.568
- Oh...
- Okay, maybe I can find room

20:21.611 --> 20:23.178
for a bite or two.

20:23.222 --> 20:24.788
- If you don't, you will
never forgive yourself.

20:24.832 --> 20:25.789
Trust me.

20:25.833 --> 20:27.617
♪ ♪

20:27.661 --> 20:30.620
[suspenseful music]

20:30.664 --> 20:37.497
♪ ♪

20:47.333 --> 20:54.296
♪ ♪

21:02.826 --> 21:04.175
- I could do this all day.

21:05.612 --> 21:06.874
All right, that wasn't fair.

21:06.917 --> 21:08.615
- Fair's got nothing
to do with it.

21:08.658 --> 21:11.139
You have to make sure you've
disarmed all your enemies.

21:11.182 --> 21:12.880
- All right, enough
with the sucker-punch lasers.

21:12.923 --> 21:14.577
- Jordan,
this is the real world.

21:14.621 --> 21:16.405
These guys will be trying
to kill you every time,

21:16.449 --> 21:17.624
and it takes one mistake

21:17.667 --> 21:20.279
to lose everything.

21:20.322 --> 21:22.324
[air booms]
- Okay, this is stupid!

21:22.368 --> 21:23.891
Every time I finish
one of your lessons,

21:23.934 --> 21:25.196
you just add another.
- Because I'm trying

21:25.240 --> 21:26.894
to keep you safe and alive.

21:26.937 --> 21:28.330
If you would stop fighting me
and just listen--

21:28.374 --> 21:29.897
- All I've done is listen

21:29.940 --> 21:31.812
and wait, and I'm sick of it!

21:31.855 --> 21:33.117
- I'm trying
to teach you something.

21:33.161 --> 21:35.163
- Yeah, but it's not about me.

21:35.206 --> 21:36.251
I just don't think
you can handle

21:36.295 --> 21:37.861
someone else being super too.

21:37.905 --> 21:39.210
[air booms]

21:39.254 --> 21:41.474
[dramatic music]

21:41.517 --> 21:43.737
[knock at door]
- It's open.

21:43.780 --> 21:45.173
It's a cylinder?

21:45.216 --> 21:46.783
It looks more
like a sad poop emoji.

21:46.827 --> 21:48.219
- Okay.
- [chuckles]

21:48.263 --> 21:49.786
- How's studying going?

21:49.830 --> 21:51.135
- Pretty great, actually.

21:51.179 --> 21:52.528
- Where's your sister?

21:52.572 --> 21:53.877
- Oh, she was hungry,
so I told her to go

21:53.921 --> 21:55.052
get something to eat.

21:55.096 --> 21:56.576
- Alone?

21:56.619 --> 21:57.968
How long ago was that?

21:58.012 --> 22:00.493
- Just, like,
right after I showed up.

22:00.536 --> 22:04.061
- About, like, an hour ago.

22:05.541 --> 22:06.803
- Uh, where's your dad?

22:06.847 --> 22:08.718
- He went to go run an errand,
I think.

22:08.762 --> 22:10.198
Mom, I'm--I'm so sorry.

22:10.241 --> 22:12.374
I, uh--
we could check the house.

22:12.418 --> 22:14.594
- We can take my truck.
- We're gonna find her.

22:14.637 --> 22:16.030
Everything is gonna be fine.

22:16.073 --> 22:17.248
I'm gonna go
to Brit and Dunn's.

22:17.292 --> 22:18.685
She probably
got into the comics

22:18.728 --> 22:20.643
and lost track of time,
so just text me.

22:20.687 --> 22:22.297
- Okay.

22:22.341 --> 22:23.298
We're good.

22:23.342 --> 22:28.651
♪ ♪

22:28.695 --> 22:30.218
[doorbell chimes]
- Thank you.

22:32.655 --> 22:33.917
Hey.

22:33.961 --> 22:35.179
There you are.

22:35.223 --> 22:36.833
I've been calling you
like crazy.

22:36.877 --> 22:38.618
- Hey, uh, sorry, yeah,

22:38.661 --> 22:40.837
I've been out of cell service.
Everything okay?

22:40.881 --> 22:43.536
- No, it's not.
Sophie's missing.

22:43.579 --> 22:45.146
- Sophie's supposed
to be at my apartment

22:45.189 --> 22:46.582
with Sarah.
- Yeah, she left

22:46.626 --> 22:48.105
and didn't come back.

22:48.149 --> 22:49.542
Why weren't you with them?

22:49.585 --> 22:51.108
- Um,

22:51.152 --> 22:52.283
I had to do a thing.

22:52.327 --> 22:54.242
- What kind of thing?

22:54.285 --> 22:55.591
- Just went on a quick hike.

22:55.635 --> 22:56.592
- A hike?

22:56.636 --> 22:58.159
- Lana, I had plans.

22:58.202 --> 23:00.161
Okay?
I'm allowed to do things,

23:00.204 --> 23:01.858
all right?
And besides, yesterday,

23:01.902 --> 23:04.252
I took Sophie to work.
- Sorry to inconvenience you

23:04.295 --> 23:06.515
with your own daughter.
- That's not what I meant.

23:06.559 --> 23:08.952
- No, what you meant was
to blame me for your mistake.

23:08.996 --> 23:10.693
- No, Lana, just--
please, listen.

23:10.737 --> 23:12.478
- You should've
been there with her,

23:12.521 --> 23:14.131
and since when
do you even hike?

23:14.175 --> 23:16.395
[object rustles]
In 20 years, you never once...

23:22.357 --> 23:23.706
Really?

23:25.491 --> 23:28.102
[sighs]
Wow.

23:28.145 --> 23:29.277
- Lana, I can explain.

23:29.320 --> 23:31.758
- No explanation necessary.

23:31.801 --> 23:33.368
I need to go find my daughter.

23:33.412 --> 23:36.719
♪ ♪

23:36.763 --> 23:37.764
[doorbell chimes]

23:41.898 --> 23:45.075
[dramatic music]

23:45.119 --> 23:46.860
[air booms]
- Jordan, come back here.

23:46.903 --> 23:48.296
- Leave me alone.
- What's going on?

23:48.339 --> 23:49.645
- Dad shot me with a laser.

23:49.689 --> 23:51.473
- What?
- He's overreacting.

23:51.517 --> 23:53.040
- Not if you shot him.

23:53.083 --> 23:54.781
But babe,
don't worry, it's fine.

23:54.824 --> 23:56.435
- How is this fine?
You're shooting our son

23:56.478 --> 23:58.045
with lasers.
- It wasn't me.

23:58.088 --> 23:59.873
It was the program,
and besides, I'm just trying

23:59.916 --> 24:01.744
to prepare him for the worst!

24:01.788 --> 24:04.530
- Okay, so then, it's just
different when it comes to me?

24:04.573 --> 24:06.270
I'm just saying,
you walked out of therapy,

24:06.314 --> 24:07.881
and you said it wasn't for you.

24:07.924 --> 24:09.752
and last night,
you walked out of our bedroom,

24:09.796 --> 24:12.233
refusing to believe
that I can die.

24:12.276 --> 24:14.061
What is going on with you?

24:14.104 --> 24:16.977
- Okay, look,
our first day at Hob's Bay,

24:17.020 --> 24:18.761
I heard about this feeling

24:18.805 --> 24:20.850
that some people with cancer

24:20.894 --> 24:23.287
experience this pull

24:23.331 --> 24:24.680
to surrender
when things get bad,

24:24.724 --> 24:26.508
like it'd just be
easier to give in,

24:26.552 --> 24:28.292
and then in the support group,
the therapist was talking about

24:28.336 --> 24:29.990
telling her husband
to let go, and--

24:30.033 --> 24:31.165
- Okay, so you're worried
I'm just gonna give up?

24:31.208 --> 24:32.645
- No, of course not.

24:32.688 --> 24:34.081
- Well, that's basically
what you implied.

24:34.124 --> 24:36.344
- No, but--I mean,
now you're writing a will

24:36.387 --> 24:37.824
and acting like
you might not make it?

24:37.867 --> 24:39.129
- Because I might not.

24:39.173 --> 24:42.350
I'm not you.
You don't get sick.

24:42.393 --> 24:44.657
Bullets literally
bounce off of you,

24:44.700 --> 24:46.702
but everyone else on Earth,
all the rest of us,

24:46.746 --> 24:48.748
could drop dead
any moment of any day,

24:48.791 --> 24:50.793
and you not acknowledging
that that's how it is

24:50.837 --> 24:52.229
isn't helping me.
- Okay, Lois,

24:52.273 --> 24:53.883
I am always going to believe

24:53.927 --> 24:55.232
that you're gonna beat this.

24:55.276 --> 24:56.538
I'm not gonna fixate

24:56.582 --> 24:58.061
on the alternative
being a possibility.

24:58.105 --> 25:00.499
- It already is.

25:02.457 --> 25:07.331
And you acting like cancer
or old age

25:07.375 --> 25:10.596
or some random bus that doesn't
see me crossing the street

25:10.639 --> 25:12.119
isn't a possibility--

25:12.162 --> 25:13.729
- Wait,
that's not what I'm saying.

25:13.773 --> 25:16.384
- But you are failing to see
that this is my reality.

25:16.427 --> 25:19.779
Cancer is my villain, Clark,

25:19.822 --> 25:23.652
and you keep acting
like it doesn't exist!

25:25.959 --> 25:27.700
- Hey, where are you going?

25:27.743 --> 25:30.920
- I'm going for a ride.
Just please don't follow me,

25:30.964 --> 25:33.314
and while I'm gone,
maybe apologize to our son

25:33.357 --> 25:37.448
for laser-beaming him
or whatever the hell that was.

25:37.492 --> 25:41.061
♪ ♪

25:41.104 --> 25:42.236
- Soph!

25:43.150 --> 25:44.543
Soph, are you here?

25:47.154 --> 25:48.677
- I checked everywhere outside.

25:48.721 --> 25:50.244
- She's not in here either.

25:50.287 --> 25:51.593
God, I can't believe
I let this happen.

25:51.637 --> 25:53.160
- Hey,
it's not all on you, okay?

25:53.203 --> 25:55.205
I was with her too.
- But she's my sister.

25:55.249 --> 25:57.904
It's like no matter
how hard I try,

25:57.947 --> 26:00.210
I can't stop screwing up
and letting my family down.

26:00.254 --> 26:01.908
- Nice try, rookie.

26:01.951 --> 26:03.257
I took space drugs
and destroyed

26:03.300 --> 26:05.389
high-school football
for the entire town.

26:05.433 --> 26:08.044
- Yeah, your massive failures
do kind of make me feel better.

26:08.088 --> 26:09.306
Don't think.

26:09.350 --> 26:10.743
What are Sophie's
favorite places?

26:10.786 --> 26:12.179
- The movie theater,

26:12.222 --> 26:14.573
but they're still playing
"Dumb Einstein"--

26:14.616 --> 26:15.835
hold up.

26:15.878 --> 26:17.184
What Soph said to my dad

26:17.227 --> 26:18.533
at the fire station--

26:18.577 --> 26:19.752
I think I know where she is.

26:19.795 --> 26:20.753
Come on.

26:20.796 --> 26:27.803
♪ ♪

26:29.805 --> 26:31.502
Oh, my God, there she is.

26:31.546 --> 26:33.156
Soph!

26:33.200 --> 26:35.724
- Leave me alone!

26:35.768 --> 26:36.899
- Sophie...

26:36.943 --> 26:38.509
- Go away.

26:39.815 --> 26:41.948
- I think I got it.

26:41.991 --> 26:42.992
Let me try.

26:43.036 --> 26:50.043
♪ ♪

26:52.741 --> 26:55.657
Last summer was
my first time at the fair.

26:55.701 --> 26:58.181
Sarah says you guys
used to go all the time.

26:58.225 --> 26:59.530
Must be tough--

26:59.574 --> 27:01.707
everything
with your mom and your dad.

27:01.750 --> 27:04.448
- Everyone always
forgets about me.

27:04.492 --> 27:06.842
They never want me around.

27:06.886 --> 27:07.887
- I know how you feel.

27:09.628 --> 27:10.629
I mean...

27:12.326 --> 27:16.330
In my family, I'm pretty much
always the one that's left out.

27:16.373 --> 27:20.595
My parents, my brother, they're
kind of a big deal, so...

27:20.639 --> 27:23.293
- Jordan's not a big deal.

27:23.337 --> 27:25.513
I mean, Sarah dumped him.

27:25.556 --> 27:27.254
- [chuckles]
That's true.

27:27.297 --> 27:29.343
You're not wrong.
- Sarah.

27:29.386 --> 27:30.736
- Dad, dad, dad, dad, dad.

27:30.779 --> 27:32.476
- I was running
yesterday back in my head--

27:32.520 --> 27:33.652
is she okay?
- She's fine, she's fine.

27:33.695 --> 27:34.696
She's fine.
She's okay.

27:34.740 --> 27:36.611
Just give 'em a second, okay?

27:36.655 --> 27:38.744
- When I first moved here,

27:38.787 --> 27:43.183
it was like everyone
from my old life was just gone,

27:43.226 --> 27:45.925
and I felt really alone.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.578
I even tried
to convince my parents

27:47.622 --> 27:49.450
to let me
move back to Metropolis.

27:49.493 --> 27:53.236
- By yourself?
- It was not a good idea.

27:53.280 --> 27:54.673
I was just upset.

27:57.676 --> 27:58.677
And...

28:00.766 --> 28:05.248
Sometimes, I just
took that out on my brother.

28:05.292 --> 28:06.293
When things got tough...

28:09.383 --> 28:11.472
He always had my back.

28:11.515 --> 28:13.300
That's what family does.

28:13.343 --> 28:15.824
- But that's your family.

28:15.868 --> 28:17.478
Mine doesn't care about me.

28:17.521 --> 28:23.397
♪ ♪

28:23.440 --> 28:25.094
I kind of doubt that.

28:27.444 --> 28:30.186
You should've seen how fast
your sister made me drive.

28:30.230 --> 28:32.754
I should probably
lose my license.

28:32.798 --> 28:34.756
- Soph, I was so worried.

28:34.800 --> 28:37.498
- We all were, hon.

28:37.541 --> 28:39.369
Come on, we gotta
get you home, okay?

28:39.413 --> 28:41.545
Your mom is probably
halfway to New Carthage now,

28:41.589 --> 28:43.330
looking for you.
- [chuckles]

28:43.373 --> 28:45.811
♪ ♪

28:45.854 --> 28:47.551
- Oh, my gosh.
You keep getting bigger.

28:47.595 --> 28:49.205
- Thank you.

28:49.249 --> 28:56.299
♪ ♪

28:59.825 --> 29:01.130
- Hey, uh...

29:02.871 --> 29:05.656
Might be a new shirt
in your future, li'l Kent.

29:05.700 --> 29:12.751
♪ ♪

29:20.062 --> 29:21.150
- I know you're mad at me.

29:21.194 --> 29:23.587
I just wanna say I'm sorry.

29:26.416 --> 29:27.809
You're a great kid.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.073
And your heart's
in the right place,

29:31.117 --> 29:32.683
and every day, I'm amazed

29:32.727 --> 29:34.903
at how far you've come.

29:34.947 --> 29:36.252
- But...
- There's no reason

29:36.296 --> 29:37.950
to rush this.

29:37.993 --> 29:39.690
Look, I've had
a lifetime of experience

29:39.734 --> 29:41.605
and plenty of mistakes
to become who I am.

29:41.649 --> 29:44.608
- Yeah, you had
to figure it out by yourself.

29:44.652 --> 29:46.567
I have Superman to learn from,

29:46.610 --> 29:48.961
and there's no better
teacher than that.

29:49.004 --> 29:51.224
[whirring]
- Superman!

29:51.267 --> 29:52.834
- What is it?

29:52.878 --> 29:54.618
- Superman!

29:54.662 --> 29:56.577
Please hurry.
- Mom.

29:56.620 --> 29:58.057
- Stay here.
[air booms]

29:58.100 --> 30:05.107
♪ ♪

30:09.851 --> 30:10.852
- Superman.

30:18.120 --> 30:19.513
- [echoing] Superman.

30:21.254 --> 30:24.039
[as Lois] Help me, Superman.

30:24.083 --> 30:27.086
[intense supersonic whirring]

30:38.532 --> 30:42.666
[intense supersonic whirring]

30:42.710 --> 30:44.538
- [grunting]

30:48.847 --> 30:51.806
[tense music]

30:51.850 --> 30:57.725
♪ ♪

30:59.205 --> 31:01.424
[screams]

31:07.343 --> 31:08.954
[whirring]

31:08.997 --> 31:10.564
- Mom, you're okay!

31:10.607 --> 31:12.174
- Yeah, why wouldn't I be?

31:12.218 --> 31:14.046
- We heard you screaming.
We thought the worst--

31:14.089 --> 31:15.482
- Okay, calm down,
and tell me what happened.

31:15.525 --> 31:16.570
- I don't know.
It sounded like you were hurt,

31:16.613 --> 31:17.745
so Dad told me to stay here,

31:17.788 --> 31:19.094
and then he left
to go find you.

31:19.138 --> 31:20.487
- You need to listen
for your father,

31:20.530 --> 31:22.619
and tell me
exactly what you hear.

31:22.663 --> 31:25.492
[intense supersonic whirring]

31:25.535 --> 31:28.451
[suspenseful music]

31:28.495 --> 31:35.545
♪ ♪

31:44.250 --> 31:45.773
- [echoing] Impressive.

31:45.816 --> 31:52.867
♪ ♪

32:02.833 --> 32:09.797
♪ ♪

32:09.840 --> 32:12.147
- [screams]

32:12.191 --> 32:13.409
- We need to call Grandpa.

32:13.453 --> 32:15.368
- The DOD won't
make it in time.

32:15.411 --> 32:16.456
You need to help him.

32:16.499 --> 32:17.500
- Dad said I wasn't ready.

32:17.544 --> 32:18.501
- Then prove him wrong.

32:18.545 --> 32:19.589
You can do this, Jordan.

32:19.633 --> 32:22.505
Go save your father.

32:22.549 --> 32:23.898
[air booms]

32:23.942 --> 32:30.949
♪ ♪

32:40.959 --> 32:47.966
♪ ♪

32:57.932 --> 33:04.983
♪ ♪

33:07.028 --> 33:08.247
- [grunts]

33:08.290 --> 33:11.424
♪ ♪

33:11.467 --> 33:12.903
- [grunts]

33:12.947 --> 33:15.428
- No!

33:15.471 --> 33:21.347
♪ ♪

33:25.090 --> 33:26.656
Jordan, Jordan,

33:26.700 --> 33:28.223
Jordan!

33:28.267 --> 33:29.833
Hey.

33:29.877 --> 33:31.226
No...

33:31.270 --> 33:32.271
No, no.

33:32.314 --> 33:34.273
No, no, Jordan, come on.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.362
Jordan.
Jordan, please.

33:36.405 --> 33:38.233
please.

33:38.277 --> 33:40.322
- [gasps]
- Oh, Jor--Jordan!

33:40.366 --> 33:43.325
[dramatic music]

33:43.369 --> 33:50.245
♪ ♪

33:55.033 --> 33:57.165
[dramatic music]

33:57.209 --> 34:00.560
- Check it out, Mom...
[door clicks]

34:00.603 --> 34:02.040
No more Musty Rusty.

34:02.083 --> 34:04.477
I'm moving up in the world.

34:04.520 --> 34:06.392
You okay?
[door clicks]

34:09.438 --> 34:11.484
- Yeah, it's okay.
- Mom, you were right.

34:11.527 --> 34:13.051
I took down
a bunch of bad guys--

34:13.094 --> 34:14.878
even got shot by Kryptonite,
but I didn't get hurt.

34:14.922 --> 34:16.750
- We're gonna run some
more tests at the fortress,

34:16.793 --> 34:18.056
but it seems like Kryptonite

34:18.099 --> 34:19.621
doesn't affect him
the same way.

34:19.666 --> 34:20.971
- What did I miss?

34:21.014 --> 34:23.322
- Oh, just Jordan
saving my life.

34:25.150 --> 34:26.498
- Li'l Kent?

34:26.542 --> 34:28.239
What, are you
the worst rapper in Kansas?

34:28.283 --> 34:31.069
- Okay, well, uh, Sarah
thought it was cool, so...

34:32.505 --> 34:34.027
- You hung out with Sarah?

34:34.072 --> 34:35.072
Yo!

34:38.032 --> 34:41.340
- I'm sorry.
- No, you were right.

34:43.559 --> 34:47.781
♪ ♪

34:47.824 --> 34:51.176
I have been
in my head a bit lately,

34:51.219 --> 34:52.742
and when I heard you
calling for help,

34:52.786 --> 34:54.353
I...

34:54.396 --> 34:55.745
I didn't even think, and...

34:58.705 --> 35:00.489
Jordan could've got hurt,

35:00.533 --> 35:03.753
but his human side of him is...

35:03.797 --> 35:05.103
that side, he got from you.

35:06.626 --> 35:08.062
It saved me.

35:08.106 --> 35:09.585
It might even make
him stronger than me.

35:09.629 --> 35:11.152
- I'm just glad
you guys are both okay.

35:11.196 --> 35:15.287
♪ ♪

35:15.330 --> 35:17.115
- When he got shot...

35:22.076 --> 35:24.731
That was
the worst moment of my life.

35:24.774 --> 35:26.211
It's like living
in a nightmare, and I...

35:29.518 --> 35:31.738
I realized I've been so
obsessed with keeping him safe,

35:31.781 --> 35:35.089
because for the first time,
I can't keep you safe.

35:35.133 --> 35:40.007
♪ ♪

35:40.050 --> 35:43.750
I feel really powerless.

35:43.793 --> 35:47.145
- Yeah, this is different
from anything we've ever faced.

35:49.973 --> 35:51.671
Even Superman has his limits.

35:51.714 --> 35:53.107
- I don't wanna lose you.

35:53.151 --> 35:57.459
♪ ♪

35:57.503 --> 35:59.157
It's terrifying.

35:59.200 --> 36:01.376
- Maybe one day,
I will feel that pull.

36:01.420 --> 36:03.117
But you have to know
I have every intention

36:03.161 --> 36:04.727
of beating this,

36:04.771 --> 36:06.555
and I will do everything I can

36:06.599 --> 36:08.775
and give everything I have

36:08.818 --> 36:10.820
to stay with you and the boys.

36:10.864 --> 36:12.822
- And I'm always gonna believe

36:12.866 --> 36:14.084
that you're gonna make it.

36:14.128 --> 36:16.565
But I promise you
I will be better

36:16.609 --> 36:19.829
at being here for you

36:19.873 --> 36:21.788
in whatever way
you need me to be.

36:21.831 --> 36:28.882
♪ ♪

36:33.060 --> 36:36.106
[coins chiming]

36:36.150 --> 36:37.673
- Aw, baby,

36:37.717 --> 36:39.327
I'm sorry.

36:39.371 --> 36:41.677
I've been so busy lately,

36:41.721 --> 36:44.071
I didn't realize how
left out you were feeling.

36:44.114 --> 36:46.943
- And I know I've been
a crappy big sister,

36:46.987 --> 36:48.162
but I was
wondering if you wanted

36:48.206 --> 36:49.642
to play video games with me.

36:49.685 --> 36:51.209
- "Zombie Cat Chasers"?

36:51.252 --> 36:52.688
- I don't really get that one,

36:52.732 --> 36:55.517
but if you do like evil pets,

36:55.561 --> 36:57.563
wait till you see
the zombie dogs.

36:59.434 --> 37:01.871
- All right, let's do it.

37:01.915 --> 37:03.830
- You don't play video games.

37:03.873 --> 37:05.092
- Excuse me,

37:05.135 --> 37:07.529
I used to crush
at "Burger Time."

37:09.531 --> 37:13.318
You know, when you climb
the ladder and make hamburgers?

37:13.361 --> 37:15.276
Yeah, I guess
it sounds pretty dumb.

37:15.320 --> 37:17.365
[laughter]

37:17.409 --> 37:18.714
- Okay, come on.
Soph, come help me

37:18.758 --> 37:20.281
get the rest
of dad's gamer stuff

37:20.325 --> 37:22.370
from the garage.
- Maybe Dad wants to play too.

37:22.414 --> 37:25.373
- You know what?
Maybe another time.

37:25.417 --> 37:26.722
- Okay.

37:26.766 --> 37:27.723
- Come on.

37:27.767 --> 37:34.817
♪ ♪

37:41.433 --> 37:42.434
- [sighs]

37:44.479 --> 37:47.830
Hey, uh, I don't know if
you're getting any of my texts

37:47.874 --> 37:50.529
or my calls--
- Kyle, I'm really glad

37:50.572 --> 37:52.226
that Sophie's okay.

37:52.270 --> 37:54.315
But I'm super busy.

37:55.795 --> 37:57.840
- Oh, okay, um,

37:57.884 --> 37:59.755
look, what happened today
with Lana, yeah,

37:59.799 --> 38:01.888
that was--it was awful,

38:01.931 --> 38:05.674
and I--I should've
just listened to you.

38:05.718 --> 38:07.676
- I know, but you didn't,

38:07.720 --> 38:10.331
so now I feel rotten,
and Lana hates me.

38:10.375 --> 38:11.332
- Chrissy,
Lana doesn't hate you.

38:11.376 --> 38:12.551
- Look, I'm pretty sure

38:12.594 --> 38:13.856
you're about to
break up with me,

38:13.900 --> 38:15.293
so why don't we just
get it over with?

38:15.336 --> 38:16.946
- [chuckles]
Whoa, whoa, no, no, no, no.

38:16.990 --> 38:20.994
That is not even close
to what's happening here.

38:21.037 --> 38:22.865
You know,
I never could've imagined

38:22.909 --> 38:25.303
finding someone
like you so fast.

38:25.346 --> 38:27.217
It took me by surprise

38:27.261 --> 38:30.438
in the best kind of way,

38:30.482 --> 38:33.572
and as far as
Lana finding out like that,

38:33.615 --> 38:35.313
it was, um,

38:35.356 --> 38:36.531
it was a shock.

38:38.098 --> 38:40.709
I promise that
she is not mad at you.

38:40.753 --> 38:43.886
- Oh, I don't want her
to be mad at you either.

38:43.930 --> 38:45.714
- Hopefully, she's not,

38:45.758 --> 38:47.890
but, um,

38:47.934 --> 38:50.458
it's complicated.

38:50.502 --> 38:53.113
- Well, where does
that leave us then?

38:53.156 --> 38:56.943
- I thought maybe we should
stop sneaking around

38:56.986 --> 38:58.988
and make this a little more,

38:59.032 --> 39:01.382
um, I don't know,

39:01.426 --> 39:03.732
public?

39:03.776 --> 39:05.343
- Okay...

39:08.998 --> 39:12.175
- Chrissy Marie Beppo,

39:12.219 --> 39:14.700
will you be my girlfriend?

39:14.743 --> 39:17.137
♪ ♪

39:17.180 --> 39:20.053
- Um...

39:20.096 --> 39:21.707
yeah.
- Mm-mm.

39:21.750 --> 39:22.882
[chuckles]

39:22.925 --> 39:24.536
[smooching]

39:24.579 --> 39:27.277
[laughs]

39:27.321 --> 39:32.239
♪ ♪

39:32.282 --> 39:34.372
- I'm glad things
are getting better.

39:37.244 --> 39:38.680
- Hi, uh, sorry.

39:38.724 --> 39:40.203
I'm, uh...
- Clark.

39:40.247 --> 39:41.553
Of course.

39:41.596 --> 39:43.729
I wasn't sure
we'd see you again.

39:43.772 --> 39:45.383
Please, come in.

39:47.297 --> 39:48.429
Your timing's perfect.

39:48.473 --> 39:50.083
Reggie just finished.

39:52.999 --> 39:54.130
Would you like to share?

39:54.174 --> 39:55.262
- Sure.

39:55.305 --> 39:56.350
Um...

39:59.484 --> 40:02.574
Hearing you story
about your husband,

40:02.617 --> 40:05.838
telling him to let go,

40:05.881 --> 40:07.927
like, I just--I couldn--
I couldn't fathom saying that

40:07.970 --> 40:09.407
to my wife.

40:10.973 --> 40:13.933
That scared me,

40:13.976 --> 40:15.325
um,

40:15.369 --> 40:16.849
in a way that I don't think

40:16.892 --> 40:18.807
I've ever been scared before.

40:20.156 --> 40:21.680
- [echoing]
Superman's still alive.

40:24.030 --> 40:27.860
[sighs]
I can't do this anymore.

40:27.903 --> 40:31.080
- That affected the way
I dealt with my family--

40:31.124 --> 40:32.647
the people more important to me

40:32.691 --> 40:35.781
than anything else
in the world.

40:35.824 --> 40:42.788
♪ ♪

40:42.831 --> 40:44.877
I find myself facing a problem

40:44.920 --> 40:48.837
that I can't do
anything about.

40:48.881 --> 40:52.450
I have no idea
what's gonna happen.

40:52.493 --> 40:54.103
There's so much we don't know--

40:54.147 --> 40:58.281
so much uncertainty.

40:58.325 --> 41:00.327
- [echoing]
My powers are fading.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.464
[normal voice]
I'm getting worse.

41:06.507 --> 41:09.510
I can feel it.
- Don't worry.

41:09.554 --> 41:12.252
Dr. Hook is so close.

41:12.295 --> 41:16.735
♪ ♪

41:16.778 --> 41:19.389
Peia...

41:19.433 --> 41:21.870
I'm going to save you.

41:21.914 --> 41:25.178
♪ ♪

41:25.221 --> 41:27.441
- What I do know is

41:27.485 --> 41:31.271
I need to be
the best version of me,

41:31.314 --> 41:33.839
so I can be there for my wife

41:33.882 --> 41:35.754
and my boys

41:35.797 --> 41:38.583
in any way they need.

41:38.626 --> 41:41.281
So that's why I'm here--

41:41.324 --> 41:43.457
to ask for help.

41:43.501 --> 41:46.416
♪ ♪

41:46.460 --> 41:49.419
[heroic music]

41:49.463 --> 41:52.597
♪ ♪
